  "prompt": "Are there legal requirements for reporting suspected money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are legal requirements for reporting suspected money laundering in many countries. Financial institutions and certain businesses are typically required to:\n\n1. Establish customer identification procedures\n2. Monitor transactions for suspicious activity\n3. File Suspicious Activity Reports (SARs) with relevant authorities\n4. Maintain transaction records\n5. Comply with anti-money laundering (AML) regulations\n\nSpecific requirements vary by jurisdiction, but most countries have established legal frameworks to detect and prevent money laundering.",
